President Obama has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Kyiv Summit on the Safe and Innovative Use of Nuclear Energy and the Chornobyl Pledging Conference in Kyiv, Ukraine. The events are being held to commemorate the 25th anniversary of the Chornobyl disaster. The delegation will be led by Dr. Zbigniew Brzezinski, former National Security Advisor to President Jimmy Carter. Other members of the delegation include U.S. Ambassador to Ukraine, John F. Tefft, and Richard L. Morningstar, Special Envoy for Eurasian Energy at the U.S. Department of State.